            {
                "s2_paper_id": "36d72b330e370d22df37397e1c10077d875ac8a2",
                "title": "Lunar Roving Adventure: Stepping into Historic Apollo Missions in Virtual Reality",
                "year": 2025,
                "venue": "Proceedings of the Special Interest Group on Computer Graphics and Interactive Techniques Conference Immersive Pavilion",
                "citation_count": 0,
                "reference_count": 2,
                "abstract": "While Moon landing missions continue to fascinate the public, younger generations may be less familiar with the Apollo program, which took place over 50 years ago. Traditional video and reading materials may feel less engaging, as they are not integrated into modern digital platforms that appeal to today\u2019s audiences. We present \u201cLunar Roving Adventure\u201d, a virtual reality game that represents the historical Apollo lunar exploration missions performed by NASA astronauts during the late 1960s and early 1970s. This game\u2019s design concepts, interactions, and game arts are relevant to historic events and factual activities. We aimed to resonate with our desire for exploration by providing a historical and educational game experience.",
                "authors": [
                    {
                        "s2_author_id": "2110911723",
